column44: We intend to sequence DNA from the zebrafish DHAB individual%2C the male double-haploid AB founder of the SAT strain. This study will deliver the AB genome assembly available and also aids to establish the genome data pool accessible within the SAT strain. In addition%2C this study will be used to establish methods to generate haplotypespecific assemblies. The data gathered here will be assembled using discovar-denovo and merged with data from a study using 10x sequencing on the same sample.%0AThis data is part of a pre-publication release. For information on the proper use of pre-publication data shared by the Wellcome Trust Sanger Institute (including details of any publication moratoria)%2C please see http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sanger.ac.uk%2Fdatasharing%2F

We intend to sequence DNA from the zebrafish DHAB individual%2C the male double-haploid AB founder of the SAT strain. This study will deliver the AB genome assembly available and also aids to establish the genome data pool accessible within the SAT strain. In addition%2C this study will be used to establish methods to generate haplotypespecific assemblies. The data gathered here will be assembled using discovar-denovo and merged with data from a study using 10x sequencing on the same sample.%0AThis data is part of a pre-publication release. For information on the proper use of pre-publication data shared by the Wellcome Trust Sanger Institute (including details of any publication moratoria)%2C please see http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sanger.ac.uk%2Fdatasharing%2F
